                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "P REcIsION farming relies on environmental monitoring wireless sensor networks to collect data on the crops and soil and then to control and optimize the use of resources, such as water and pesticides. Thanks to the advancement of ultralow power computing paradigms and hardware [1], more environmentally friendly and maintenance- free supply solutions are gaining momentum, such as in battery- free electronics [2], [3]. Typically, battery- free devices [4] harvest energy from the environment and store it in a supercapacitor, sporadically executing tasks [5] whenever energy is sufficient, in an intermittent fashion [6]."
                                }
                            ]
